Dedication

This work is published in honor of Professor Robert Gateman, UBC Economics.
For decades, Professor Gateman taught introductory economics to first-year
students at the University of British Columbia, and gave them — alongside
supply and demand — a four-rule posture toward knowledge that this skill
attempts to translate into software and AI practice:

    "Assume nothing, question everything, worship no one,
     and applaud humility."

He ended every lecture the same way:

    "Go make a difference."

Tuum Est.
